<%= content_for :page_title, "New features coming to Publish" %>

<h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">
  New features coming to Publish
</h1>
<div class="govuk-grid-row">
  <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
    <p class="govuk-body">Here’s a list of features we’ve recently added to Publish teacher training courses, followed by the features we plan to add in the next few months. </p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Your courses for 2020 - 2021</h2>

    <p class="govuk-body">In July we rolled over your courses for 2020 – 2021. You can currently:</p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>edit the detailed descriptions of your courses (the content in the 'About this course' section)</li>
      <li>add a new location (<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=W_zhfemKiYM" class="govuk-link">watch a video<span class="govuk-visually-hidden">of the assigning locations feature</span></a> showing how to do this)</li>
      <li>edit location details</li>
      <li>assign locations to a course</li>
      <li>request a new course using a Google Form</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="govuk-body">Within the ‘Basic details’ section of your courses, you can edit:</p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>subjects</li>
      <li>vacancies (<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nxmtXGy1cCY" class="govuk-link">watch a video<span class="govuk-visually-hidden">of the edit vacancies feature</span></a> showing how to do this)</li>
      <li>outcome</li>
      <li>age range</li>
      <li>start date</li>
      <li>UCAS Apply eligibility requirements and application opening date</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="govuk-body">In Basic details, you can also specify if the course:</p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>is fee paying or salaried</li>
      <li>is full time or part time</li>
      <li>is an apprenticeship</li>
      <li>has a Special educational needs and disability (SEND) specialism</li>
      <li>has an accredited body</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="govuk-heading-l">Later in 2020</h3>

    <p class="govuk-body">You’ll be able to:</p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>add a new course directly in Publish</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
